@therealblkraptor
If those games were a sort of almost-charity for poor kids, there'd be no reason to make them look like the PSP, PS3, GBA SP etc., to sell them for much much more than they are worth and to package three of what's essentially the same game with slightly altered graphics.
I don't mind the cheap-but-honest variety, but these knock offs are designed to fool people (mainly parents who don't know any better, I guess).

@therealblkraptor 

and yet you think it's right to exploit the chinese by repackaging the same games 500 times and making them seem different on the outside?

doubt it.
